  "virtualization-adapters-guide.md": "# Virtualization Adapters Guide

Generated by Crucible v1.0.0 | Theme: soft | Framework: vue

This guide explains how to integrate external virtualization libraries with the Table component using the \`customVirtualState\` escape hatch.

---

## Overview

The Table component includes a **headless virtualization system** based on \`HeadlessVirtualizer\` - a framework-agnostic class that provides basic virtual scrolling without any UI dependencies. This allows:

1. **Zero-dependency** out-of-the-box virtualization
2. **Easy migration** to feature-rich libraries when needed
3. **Plug-and-play** integration with any virtualization library

---


## Vue Integration

### Using vue-virtual-scroller

vue-virtual-scroller is the most popular virtualization library for Vue 3:

\`\`\`vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref, computed } from 'vue';
import { Table } from './Table';
import type { VirtualState } from './utils/virtualizer';

interface Props {
  data: YourDataType[];
  columns: TableColumn[];
}

const props = defineProps<Props>();

const containerRef = ref<HTMLElement | null>(null);

// Dynamic scroller configuration
const dynamicScrollerRef = ref<any>(null);

const customVirtualState = computed<VirtualState>(() => {
  const totalItems = props.data.length;
  const itemHeight = 44;
  const containerHeight = 600;
  
  // Get from DynamicScroller if available
  if (dynamicScrollerRef.value) {
    const firstVisible = dynamicScrollerRef.value.getFirstVisible();
    return {
      startIndex: firstVisible?.index ?? 0,
      endIndex: Math.min(totalItems - 1, firstVisible?.index + Math.ceil(containerHeight / itemHeight)),
      totalHeight: totalItems * itemHeight,
      offsetY: firstVisible?.offsetTop ?? 0,
      virtualItems: Array.from({ length: Math.ceil(containerHeight / itemHeight) + 5 }, (_, i) => ({
        index: (firstVisible?.index ?? 0) + i,
        start: ((firstVisible?.index ?? 0) + i) * itemHeight,
      })),
    };
  }
  
  return {
    startIndex: 0,
    endIndex: Math.min(totalItems - 1, Math.ceil(containerHeight / itemHeight)),
    totalHeight: totalItems * itemHeight,
    offsetY: 0,
    virtualItems: Array.from({ length: Math.ceil(containerHeight / itemHeight) }, (_, i) => ({
      index: i,
      start: i * itemHeight,
    })),
  };
});
</script>

<template>
  <Table
    :columns="columns"
    :data="data"
    row-key="id"
    :virtualize="true"
    :custom-virtual-state="customVirtualState"
  />
</template>
\`\`\`

### Using @pdanpdan/virtual-scroll

\`\`\`vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref, computed } from 'vue';
import { Table } from './Table';
import type { VirtualState } from './utils/virtualizer';

interface Props {
  data: YourDataType[];
  columns: TableColumn[];
}

const props = defineProps<Props>();

const virtualScrollRef = ref<any>(null);

const customVirtualState = computed<VirtualState>(() => {
  if (!virtualScrollRef.value) {
    return {
      startIndex: 0,
      endIndex: props.data.length - 1,
      totalHeight: props.data.length * 44,
      offsetY: 0,
      virtualItems: props.data.map((_, i) => ({ index: i, start: i * 44 })),
    };
  }

  const state = virtualScrollRef.value.getState();
  return {
    startIndex: state.start ?? 0,
    endIndex: state.end ?? props.data.length - 1,
    totalHeight: state.total ?? props.data.length * 44,
    offsetY: state.offset ?? 0,
    virtualItems: state.items?.map((item: any) => ({
      index: item.index,
      start: item.start,
    })) ?? [],
  };
});
</script>

<template>
  <Table
    :columns="columns"
    :data="data"
    row-key="id"
    :virtualize="true"
    :custom-virtual-state="customVirtualState"
  />
</template>
\`\`\`

### Custom VirtualState from Scratch

\`\`\`vue
<script setup lang="ts">
import { ref, computed, onMounted, onUnmounted } from 'vue';
import { Table } from './Table';
import type { VirtualState } from './utils/virtualizer';

interface Props {
  data: YourDataType[];
  columns: TableColumn[];
}

const props = defineProps<Props>();

const containerRef = ref<HTMLElement | null>(null);
const scrollTop = ref(0);
const containerHeight = ref(600);
const itemHeight = 44;

const virtualState = computed<VirtualState>(() => {
  const startIndex = Math.max(0, Math.floor(scrollTop.value / itemHeight) - 5);
  const endIndex = Math.min(
    props.data.length - 1,
    Math.ceil((scrollTop.value + containerHeight.value) / itemHeight) + 5
  );

  const virtualItems = [];
  for (let i = startIndex; i <= endIndex; i++) {
    virtualItems.push({ index: i, start: i * itemHeight });
  }

  return {
    startIndex,
    endIndex,
    totalHeight: props.data.length * itemHeight,
    offsetY: startIndex * itemHeight,
    virtualItems,
  };
});

const handleScroll = (e: Event) => {
  scrollTop.value = (e.target as HTMLElement).scrollTop;
};

onMounted(() => {
  if (containerRef.value) {
    const observer = new ResizeObserver((entries) => {
      containerHeight.value = entries[0].contentRect.height;
    });
    observer.observe(containerRef.value);
  }
});
</script>

<template>
  <Table
    :columns="columns"
    :data="data"
    row-key="id"
    :virtualize="true"
    :custom-virtual-state="virtualState"
  />
</template>
\`\`\`

---

## API Reference

### VirtualState Interface

\`\`\`typescript
export interface VirtualState {
  startIndex: number;      // First visible item index
  endIndex: number;        // Last visible item index
  totalHeight: number;     // Total scrollable height
  offsetY: number;         // Y offset for positioning
  virtualItems: {          // Array of visible items
    index: number;         // Item index in data array
    start: number;         // Y position of item
  }[];
}
\`\`\`

### Table Props for Virtualization

| Prop | Type | Description |
|------|------|-------------|
| \`virtualize\` | \`boolean\` | Enable virtualization |
| \`virtualizationThreshold\` | \`number\` | Min items before virtualizing (default: 100) |
| \`itemHeight\` | \`number\` | Height of each row in pixels (default: 44) |
| \`customVirtualState\` | \`VirtualState\` | External virtualization state |

---

## Migration from HeadlessVirtualizer

If you started with the built-in \`HeadlessVirtualizer\` and need more features:

1. **Install vue-virtual-scroller**: \`npm install vue-virtual-scroller\`
2. **Create the virtualizer** with your template ref
3. **Map the state** to \`VirtualState\` interface using computed
4. **Pass to Table** via \`custom-virtual-state\` prop
5. **Remove** or keep built-in props for fallback behavior

The DOM structure stays the same - only the state source changes!



---

## Common Issues & Solutions

### 1. Row Height Mismatch

**Problem**: Rows don't align with virtual positions.

**Solution**: Ensure \`itemHeight\` in your adapter matches actual row height:
\`\`\`typescript
// Match the actual CSS row height
const itemHeight = 44; // Check your CSS!
\`\`\`

### 2. Scroll Position Reset

**Problem**: Scroll position jumps when switching virtualizers.

**Solution**: Sync scroll positions before switching:
\`\`\`typescript
const scrollTop = containerRef.current?.scrollTop ?? 0;
// Set external virtualizer to same position
externalVirtualizer.scrollTo(scrollTop);
\`\`\`

### 3. Empty or Missing Rows

**Problem**: Some rows don't render.

**Solution**: Check \`virtualItems\` mapping:
\`\`\`typescript
// Ensure index maps correctly
virtualItems: rowVirtualizer.getVirtualItems().map(item => ({
  index: item.index,  // This should match data array index
  start: item.start,
}))
\`\`\`

---

## Performance Tips

1. **Memoize VirtualState**: Use \`useMemo\` (React) / \`computed\` (Vue) / \`computed\` (Angular)
2. **Debounce Scroll Handlers**: Avoid excessive state updates
3. **Use Overscan**: Render extra items to prevent blank areas during fast scroll
4. **Profile with DevTools**: Check FPS during scroll to ensure 60fps

---

## Related Files

- \`utils/virtualizer.ts\` - HeadlessVirtualizer implementation
- \`utils/table-sorter.ts\` - Sorting utilities
- \`utils/table-paginator.ts\` - Pagination utilities

---

